From: Aditya Pakki <pakki001@umn.edu>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2020 20:29:18 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] drm/nouveau: fix reference count leak in
 nv50_disp_atomic_commit
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.8.6
Git-commit: a2cdf39536b0d21fb06113f5e16692513d7bcb9c

[ Upstream commit a2cdf39536b0d21fb06113f5e16692513d7bcb9c ]

nv50_disp_atomic_commit() calls calls pm_runtime_get_sync and in turn
increments the reference count. In case of failure, decrement the
ref count before returning the error.

Signed-off-by: Aditya Pakki <pakki001@umn.edu>
Signed-off-by: Ben Skeggs <bskeggs@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/dispnv50/disp.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/dispnv50/disp.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/dispnv50/disp.c
index 800b7757252e..d2c2d102e732 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/dispnv50/disp.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/dispnv50/disp.c
@@ -2160,8 +2160,10 @@ nv50_disp_atomic_commit(struct drm_device *dev,
 	int ret, i;
 
 	ret = pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->dev);
-	if (ret < 0 && ret != -EACCES)
+	if (ret < 0 && ret != -EACCES) {
+		pm_runtime_put_autosuspend(dev->dev);
 		return ret;
+	}
 
 	ret = drm_atomic_helper_setup_commit(state, nonblock);
 	if (ret)
